ty.org/org/news/2003/031217-uzi.htm |title=Israel's army phases out country's iconic Uzi submachine gun |website=Globalsecurity.org |date=17 December 2003 |accessdate=22 August 2010 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090312070515/http://www.globalsecurity.org/org/news/2003/031217-uzi.htm |archivedate=12 March 2009 |url-status=live }}</ref> Being replaced by [[IMI Tavor]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thefirearmblog.com/blog/2012/12/18/idf-reserve-units-switching-from-m16-to-tavor/|title=IDF Reserve Units Switching From M16 To Tavor|author1=Johnson, Steve |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121230191250/http://www.thefirearmblog.com/blog/2012/12/18/idf-reserve-units-switching-from-m16-to-tavor/ |archivedate=30 December 2012 |website=TheFireArmBlog.com|date=18 December 2012|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Ivory Coast}}<ref>{{cite book|title=Identifier les sources d'approvisionnement: Les munitions de petit calibre en C\u00f4te d'Ivoire|url=http://www.smallarmssurvey.org/fileadmin/docs/C-Special-reports/SAS-SR21-CotedIvoire-FR.pdf|first=Holger|last=Anders|date=June 2014|publisher=[[Small Arms Survey]] and [[United Nations Operation in C\u00f4te d'Ivoire]]|isbn=978-2-940-548-05-7|page=15|language=fr|access-date=5 September 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181009093415/http://www.smallarmssurvey.org/fileadmin/docs/C-Special-reports/SAS-SR21-CotedIvoire-FR.pdf|archive-date=9 October 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Japan}}: M16A1 is used by [[Western Army Infantry Regiment]] along with [[Howa Type 89]] rifles.<ref name=\"SAT Structure\">{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131104200548/http://www.kjclub.com/jp/exchange/photo/read.php?tname=exc_board_53&uid=5386&fid=5386&thread=1000000&idx=1&page=1&number=4103 |archivedate=4 November 2013 |script-title=ja:\u65e5\u672c\u306e\u7279\u6b8a\u90e8\u968a |url=http://www.kjclub.com/jp/exchange/photo/read.php?tname=exc_board_53&uid=5386&fid=5386&thread=1000000&idx=1&page=1&number=4103 |language=Japanese |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* {{flag|Jamaica}}<ref name=ewen2005 />\n* {{flag|Jordan}}<ref name=ewen2005 /> M16A1/A2\n* {{flag|Nicaragua}}: Used by the [[National Police of Nicaragua]] and army.<ref>https://havanatimes.org/news/ortegas-nicaraguan-police-train-for-a-civil-war/</ref>\n* {{flag|North Korea}}: M16A1 (probably unlicensed copies) used by KPA special forces. Used during the [[1996 Gangneung submarine infiltration incident|Gangneung incident in 1996]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://imnews.imbc.com/20dbnews/history/1996/2001702_13448.html |work=MBC News |title=A Weapon Displayed From North Korea Special Forces and their Submarine |date=25 September 1996 |access-date=3 June 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181020071905/http://imnews.imbc.com/20dbnews/history/1996/2001702_13448.html |archive-date=20 October 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://bemil.chosun.com/nbrd/gallery/view.html?b_bbs_id=10044&pn=1&num=177361 |work=Yu Yong-won's Military World, Chosun Ilbo |title=Equipment of North Korean Special Forces and Espionage |date=16 April 2013 |access-date=3 June 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150524023732/http://bemil.chosun.com/nbrd/gallery/view.html?b_bbs_id=10044&pn=1&num=177361 |archive-date=24 May 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n* {{flag|South Korea}}: During the [[Vietnam War]], the U.S. provided 27,000 M16 rifles to the [[Republic of Korea Armed Forces]] in [[Vietnam]]. Also, 600,000 M16A1s (Colt Model 603K) were manufactured under license by [[S&T Daewoo|Daewoo Precision Industries]] with deliveries from 1974 to 1985.<ref name=ewen2005 /> KATUSA (Korean Augmentation to the U.S. Army) soldiers who serve in the U.S. Army use the M16A2.{{citation needed|date=July 2018}}\n* {{flag|Kuwait}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sites.google.com/site/worldinventory/wiw_me_kuwait |title=wiw_me_kuwait \u2013 worldinventory|website=sites.google.com}}</ref> M16A1/A2.\n* {{flag|Latvia}}:<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sites.google.com/site/worldinventory/wiw_eu_latvia|title=wiw_eu_latvia \u2013 worldinventory|website=sites.google.com|access-date=15 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161124202703/https://sites.google.com/site/worldinventory/wiw_eu_latvia|archive-date=24 November 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Lebanon}}<ref name=worldpolicy2000 /> M16A1<ref name=mcnab2002>{{cite book |last=McNab |first=Chris |title=20th Century Military Uniforms |year=2002 |edition=2nd |publisher=Grange Books |location=Kent |isbn=978-1-84013-476-6|page=174}}</ref>/A2/A4.\n* {{flag|Lesotho}}<ref name=ewen2005 />\n* {{flag|Liberia}}<ref name=worldpolicy2000 /> M16A2\n* {{flag|Lithuania}}: [[Lithuanian Armed Forces]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://kariuomene.kam.lt/lt/ginkluote_ir_karine_technika/automatiniai_sautuvai/automatinis_sautuvas_m-16.html |title=Lietuvos kariuomen\u0117 :: Ginkluot\u0117 ir karin\u0117 technika \u00bbAutomatiniai \u0161autuvai\u00bb Automatinis \u0161autuvas M-16 |publisher=Kariuomene.kam.lt |date=17 April 2009 |accessdate=22 August 2010 |language=lt |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100328132948/http://kariuomene.kam.lt/lt/ginkluote_ir_karine_technika/automatiniai_sautuvai/automatinis_sautuvas_m-16.html |archive-date=28 March 2010 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n* {{flag|Malaysia}}<ref name=ewen2005 /> [[Malaysian Armed Forces]], [[Royal Malaysia Police]], [[Malaysian Maritime Enforcement Agency]] and [[RELA Corps]].\n* {{flag|Mauritius}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fazsoi.defense.gouv.fr/les-fazsoi/breves/55-sauvetage-au-combat-de-niveau-1-sc1-a-l-ile-maurice.html?highlight=YTozOntpOjA7czozOiJpbGUiO2k6MTtzOjc6Im1hdXJpY2UiO2k6MjtzOjExOiJpbGUgbWF1cmljZSI7fQ==|title=Sauvetage au combat de niveau 1 [SC1] \u00e0 l'\u00eele Maurice|date=12 December 2012|publisher=Forces Arm\u00e9es de la Zone Sud de l'Oc\u00e9an Indien|language=French|accessdate=24 October 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130922143819/http://www.fazsoi.de