fs/NAVA-IB2-Legacies-of-War.pdf|archive-date=8 July 2014|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Netherlands}}: C7 and C8 variants are used by the [[Armed forces of the Netherlands|Military of the Netherlands]] and [[Diemaco C7LSW|LSW]] is used by [[Netherlands Marine Corps]].<ref name=miller2001 /><ref>{{cite book |author1=Bartocci, Christopher R.|date=2004|title=Black Rifle II The M16 into the 21st Century|publisher=Collector Grade Publications Incorporated |isbn=0-88935-348-4}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Nicaragua}}<ref name=ewen2005 />\n* {{flag|Nigeria}}<ref name=ewen2005 />\n* {{flag|Oman}}<ref name=ewen2005 />\n* {{flag|Pakistan}}<ref name=ewen2005 /> M16A1\n* {{flag|Palestinian Authority}}: Used by [[Palestinian National Security Forces|Palestinian Security Forces]]<ref>{{cite web |author=Adnan Abu Amer |url=http://www.al-monitor.com/pulse/originals/2015/05/palestine-gaza-security-services-annual-budget-finance-aman.html |title=Security services drain Palestine's budget |publisher=Al-Monitor |date=10 May 2015 |accessdate=8 June 2017 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170505024245/http://www.al-monitor.com/pulse/originals/2015/05/palestine-gaza-security-services-annual-budget-finance-aman.html |archivedate=5 May 2017 }}</ref> and various local militant forces.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/in_pictures/6121208.stm|title=In pictures: Gaza offensive|work=BBC News|date=6 November 2006|access-date=20 March 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180320231201/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/in_pictures/6121208.stm|archive-date=20 March 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.worthynews.com/3354-hamas-fighting-with-weapons-from-israel-investigation|title=Hamas Fighting With Weapons From Israel (Investigation)|date=6 January 2009|access-date=20 March 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180320230451/https://www.worthynews.com/3354-hamas-fighting-with-weapons-from-israel-investigation|archive-date=20 March 2018|u