erationandCycleofFunctioningTF93663|name=\"Rifle 5.56mm, XM16E1, Operation and Cycle of Functioning TF9-3663 (1966)\"}}\n* {{Internet Archive short film|id=gov.dod.dimoc.28805|name=\"Rifle, M16A1 \u2013 Part II \u2013 Field Expedients (1 July 1968)\"}}\n* {{Internet Archive short film|id=gov.archives.arc.36901|name=\"Fundamentals of Rifle Marksmanship (1971)\"}}\n* {{Internet Archive short film|id=gov.ntis.ava21011vnb1|name=\"Fundamentals of Rifle Marksmanship (1999)\"}}\n* [http://wayback.vefsafn.is/wayback/20050302221655/http://www.ar15.com/content/manuals/TM9-1005-319-10.pdf Operator's Manual for Rifle, 5.56 mm, M16A2; Rifle 5.56 mm, M16A3; Rifle, 5.56 mm, M16A4; Carbine, 5.56 mm, M4; Carbine, 5.56 mm, M4A1]\n* [http://www.bimbel.de/artikel/artikel-25.html M16 in parts] (German)\n* [http://www.retroblackrifle.com/ Early M16 rifles]\n{{div col end}}\n\n{{ModernUKInfWeaponsNav}}\n{{ModernUSInfWeaponsNav}}\n{{Colt's Manufacturing Company}}\n{{ArmaLite AR-10 derivatives}}\n{{USAF Weapons}}\n\n[[Category:ArmaLite AR-10 derivatives]]\n[[Category:5.56\u00d745mm NATO assault rifles]]\n[[Category:Infantry weapons of the Cold War]]\n[[Category:Rifles of the Cold War]]\n[[Category:Colt rifles]]\n[[Category:Rifles of the United States]]\n[[Category:United States Marine Corps equipment]]\n[[Category:Weapons and ammunition introduced in 1964]]\n[[Category:AR-15 style rifles]]\n[[Category:Gas-operated firearms]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|Military assault rifle}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox weapon\n| name         = Rifle, Caliber 5.56&nbsp;mm, M16\n| image        = File:M16a1m16a2m4m16a45wi.jpg\n| image_size   = 300\n| caption      = From top to bottom: M16A1, M16A2, [[M4 carbine|M4A1]], M16A4\n| origin       = United States <!-- WP:INFOBOXFLAG -->\n| type         = [[Assault rifle]]\n<!-- Type selection -->\n| is_ranged    = Yes\n<!-- Service history -->\n| service      = 1964\u2013present<ref name=\"autogenerated5\" />\n| used_by      = See ''[[