licy2000 />\n* {{flag|Somalia}}<ref name=ewen2005 />\n* {{flag|South Africa}}: Used by [[South African Special Forces Brigade|Special Forces]].<ref name=ewen2005 /> Likely received from Moroccan stocks.<ref name=\"Morocco-ZA\">{{cite web |title=History 'lesson' of note at Arts Festival |url=http://www.knysnaplettherald.com/news/Arts--Entertainment/Entertainment/173686/History-lesson-of-note-at-Arts-Festival|location=Dammam\n|publisher=Knysna-Plett Herald|date=6 October 2016|accessdate=22 December 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161222134619/http://www.knysnaplettherald.com/news/Arts--Entertainment/Entertainment/173686/History-lesson-of-note-at-Arts-Festival|archivedate=22 December 2016}}</ref>\n* {{flag|Sri Lanka}}<ref>{{cite book | last= Smith | first= Chris | title= In the Shadow of a Cease-fire: The Impacts of Small Arms Availability and Misuse in Sri Lanka | publisher= Small Arms Survey | date= October 2003 | url= http://www.smallarmssurvey.org/fileadmin/docs/B-Occasional-papers/SAS-OP11-Sri-Lanka.pdf | series= Occasional Paper No. 11 | page= 13 | access-date= 6 September 2018 | archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20170705130927/http://www.smallarmssurvey.org/fileadmin/docs/B-Occasional-papers/SAS-OP11-Sri-Lanka.pdf | archive-date= 5 July 2017 | url-status= live }}</ref>\n* {{flag|Sweden}} A small number of M16A2s are used by the [[Swedish Armed Forces]] for familiarization training, as well as a similar number of AKMs, but they are not issued to combat units.<ref>{{cite web |author=Henrik Svensk |url=http://www.soldf.com/utlvap.html |title=M16 M16A2 Kalashnikov AK-47 \u2013 Utl\u00e4ndska Vapensatsen |publisher=SoldF.com |language=Swedish |accessdate=13 July 2014|quote=The foreign weapons kit was purchased in 1986 to give personnel in the Armed Forces the opportunity to get to know the weapons that usually show up in war and crisis situations|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160410075842/https://www.soldf.com/utlvap.html |archivedate=