rtford, Marshall Cavendish (London) 1985\n* Afonso, Aniceto and Gomes, Carlos de Matos, ''Guerra Colonial'' (2000), {{ISBN|972-46-1192-2}}\n* Bartocci, Christopher R. ''Black Rifle II The M16 into the 21st Century''. Cobourg, Ontario, Canada: Collector Grade Publications Incorporated, 2004. {{ISBN|0-88935-348-4}}\n* {{Cite book|first=Edward Clinton |last=Ezell |year=1984 |title=The Great Rifle Controversy: Search for the Ultimate Infantry Weapon from World War II Through Vietnam and Beyond |location=[[Harrisburg, Pennsylvania|Harrisburg]], Pennsylvania |publisher=Halsted Press |isbn=978-0-8117-0709-1}}\n* {{Cite book|first=David R. |last=Hughes |year=1990 |title=The History and Development of the M16 Rifle and its Cartridge |location=[[Oceanside, California|Oceanside]], California |publisher=Armory Publications|isbn=978-0-9626096-0-2}}\n* Hutton, Robert, ''The .223'', Guns & Ammo Annual Edition, 1971.\n* McNaugher, Thomas L. \"[https://www.rand.org/pubs/papers/P6306/ Marksmanship, Mcnamara and the M16 Rifle: Organisations, Analysis and Weapons Acquisition]\"\n* {{Cite journal |author=M16 Rifle Review Panel |title=Report of the M16 Rifle Review Panel |date=1 June 1968 |url=http://www.dtic.mil/cgi-bin/GetTRDoc?AD=ADA953110 |id=ADA953110 |publisher=Chief of Staff U.S. Army }}\n* Pikula, Sam (Major), ''The ArmaLite AR-10'', 1998\n* Rose, Alexander. ''American Rifle-A Biography.'' 2008; Bantam Dell Publishing. {{ISBN|978-0-553-80517-8}}.\n* Stevens, R. Blake and Edward C. Ezell. ''The Black Rifle M16 Retrospective''. Enhanced second printing. Cobourg, Ontario, Canada: Collector Grade Publications Incorporated, 1994. {{ISBN|0-88935-115-5}}\n* Urdang, Laurence, Editor in Chief. ''The Random House Dictionary of the English Language.'' 1969; Random House/New York.\n* U.S. Army; Sadowski, Robert A., Editor. ''The M16A1 Rifle: Operation and Preventive Maintenance'' Enhanced, hardcover edition 2013; Skyhorse, New York, NY. {{ISBN|1616088648}}\n{{Refend}}\n\n==External links==\n